<div class="section" id="intel-virtual-usa-or-canada">
<h2><a class="reference external" href="http://www.Intel.com">Intel</a> (Virtual USA or Canada)</h2>
<p><em>Posted 13-February-2013</em></p>
<p><strong>Job Description</strong>:</p>
<p>We are recruiting for Contract Python Engineers based in either the US or Canada.
Candidate will work in a small group with Intel Corporation's High Performance Data Division.
You will have full responsibility for delivery of technical solutions (design, implementation, and test).</p>
<p>Please provide your code samples along with your resume and hourly rate.</p>
<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul class="simple">
<li>Solid Python and software engineering skills</li>
<li>Deep Acumen with AWS is required</li>
<li>Strong knowledge of Linux operating system and experience in hosting Web applications on this platform</li>
<li>Experience writing enterprise production software in Python</li>
<li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science with 4-7 years of relevant practical experience</li>
<li>Team player with excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
<li>Ability to excel in a fast-paced, fast-growth environment where using your initiative, experience, and intuition are prerequisites to performing well</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About the company</strong></p>
<p>The Intel Software and Services Group (SSG) connects Intel to the
worldwide software community.  SSG strives to bring competitive
advantage to Intel platforms by helping independent software vendors,
operating system developers, OEMs, channel members and systems
integrators deliver exceptional customer value and achieve
differentiation on Intel processor technologies. SSG provides global
leadership to the software community through its technical expertise,
industry enabling activities, and developer products and
programs. These positions will be working for the High Performance
Data Division (HPDD).</p>
<p><strong>Contact Info:</strong></p>
<ul class="simple">
<li><strong>Contact</strong>: P. Hunt Technical Recruiter</li>
<li><strong>E-mail contact</strong>: <a class="reference external" href="mailto:penny&#37;&#52;&#48;planetworkforce&#46;com">penny<span>&#64;</span>planetworkforce<span>&#46;</span>com</a></li>
<li><strong>Telecommuting OK</strong></li>
</ul>
</div>
