<div class="section" id="crunch-io-san-francisco-ca-usa">
<h2><a class="reference external" href="http://crunch.io">Crunch.io</a> (San Francisco, CA, USA)</h2>
<p><em>Posted 12-February-2013</em></p>
<p><strong>Job Description</strong>:</p>
<p>Crunch.io seeks a Senior RESTful Service Engineer to lead the development of our collaborative platform for advanced analytics. You will be responsible for our platform's public API and the business logic that sits behind it. You will shape the application's design from the early stages, putting us on a solid foundation for rapid growth. By doing so, you and your teammates will transform the way people think about exploring and analyzing data.</p>
<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>This position is right for you if:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li>You have at least 8 years of serious programming experience, and at least 4 using Python. By &quot;serious&quot;, we mean applications with complex logic, heavy usage, and no tolerance for errors.</li>
<li>You don't just speak HTTP fluently: you're often mistaken for a native speaker. You know that HTTP is more than just a transport for HTML.</li>
<li>You've built APIs that served multiple client applications. Your friends are probably tired of hearing you talk about how superior RESTful services are. (Don't worry, we'll never tire of it.)</li>
<li>You measure people by their test coverage.</li>
<li>You've worked with CherryPy and aren't afraid to dive into _cptools. No CherryPy experience? Having worked with Flask, web2py, Tornado, Werkzeug, Bottle, or circuits.web may help.</li>
<li>You can provide examples of your work that demonstrate all of the above.</li>
<li>You have strong oral and written communication skills and believe that an idea that can't be expressed clearly to your peers isn't yet a good idea.</li>
<li>You have a degree in computer science or related field.</li>
