<p>First and foremost, we're looking for people who enjoy programming,
take pride in their work, and have an ability to develop
database-driven web applications as part of a team that includes
technical and non-technical people.</p>
<p>From that, it follows that an ideal candidate would probably have many
of the below attributes:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li>At least a Bachelor's degree, preferably in computer science</li>
<li>Experience with Python (our primary development language),
relational databases, SQL (PostgreSQL or ANSI SQL preferred),
Unix/Linux/OS X command line work, common web standards and
technologies like HTTP and JavaScript, version control (Git is a
plus)</li>
<li>Personable with good communication skills, since part of your duties
will involve interfacing with users and customers</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About the company</strong></p>
<p>Socialserve.com is a 501(c)(3) registered non-profit, founded in 1999
to leverage IT to help people in need and to increase the efficiency
of governments and other organizations.  Technology is at the core of
our company, and we aim to provide a flexible and interesting
environment for our developers.</p>
